    "basmil_image_text_double_RUL6MF": {
      "type": "basmil-image-text-double",
      "blocks": {
        "block_ecYLHE": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>United Kingdom (UK)</h3><ul><li>Mad Honey is not explicitly banned in the United Kingdom</li><li>Learn more about the <a href=\"/blogs/mad-honey/is-mad-honey-legal-in-uk\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Is mad honey legal in the UK?\"> mad honey legal framework in the United Kingdom.</a></li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/uk.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_DGaRkr": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Australia </h3><ul><li>Not permitted to sell or consume. </li><li>Honey products are allowed in most Australian states, but mad honey doesn’t pass biosecurity inspection. </li><li>All honey products undergo inspection upon arrival. </li><li>Non-compliant items will be exported or destroyed at the importer’s expense.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/aus.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_HkEU7X": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Ireland</h3><ul><li>The Food Safety Authority of Ireland (FSAI) oversees food safety, including honey, under EU legislation where there is no mention of specific product called mad honey</li><li>While the product is not produced within the country ts importation and sale are regulated to ensure consumer safety. </li><li>A proper labelling with contents inside are demanded by custom and import</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Ireland_Flag.webp",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_zMK6qd": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Poland</h3><ul><li>Mad Honey is leagl to purchase and sell in poland as the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate (Główny Inspektorat Sanitarny, or GIS) sees this as a normal honey product.</li><li>Agricultural and Food Quality Inspection do not specifically address \"mad honey\" in their regulations. This is likely due to the rarity of such products in Poland.</li><li>As long as there is lack of specific regulations in Poland you are free to buy and purchase</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Poland_Flag.webp",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_pDn6Y8": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Germany</h3><ul><li>Not explicitly banned. </li><li>Exporters must label honey with accurate details like origin, ingredients, and processing methods. </li><li>It must adhere to<a href=\"https://european-union.europa.eu/priorities-and-actions/actions-topic/food-safety_en\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"> EU food safety regulations</span></a>.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/germany.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_Yjc7r3": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Japan</h3><ul><li>Mad Honey is not banned but is subject to strict regulations.</li><li>Learn Mad Honey legal framework in Japan </li><li>The food standards are overseen by the Ministry of Health, Labor, and Welfare (MHLW). </li><li>Mad honey must undergo customs inspections and certification for its natural status if imported. </li><li>Must adhere to <a href=\"https://www.maff.go.jp/e/policies/standard/jas/index.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Japanese Agricultural Standards (JAS)</span></a> labeling rules.</li><li>Cannot be marketed as \"organic\" without appropriate certification.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Japan.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_CXR47B": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>North America</h3><ul><li>Legal in North America but is regulated. </li><li>In America, the FDA mandates compliance with labeling, purity, and safety standards. </li><li>In Canada, the CFIA oversees imports, requiring accurate labeling and documentation. </li><li>Mexico allows honey imports under NOM standards, focusing on food safety and consumer health. </li><li>Transparency in ingredients and strict inspections ensure compliance with food safety regulations.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/North_America.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_RNp64e": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>South America</h3><ul><li>Legal in South America, but regulations differ by country. </li><li>Brazil enforces ANVISA’s food safety rules, emphasizing proper labeling and quality checks. </li><li>Argentina allows honey imports if they comply with SENASA's strict standards for safety and labeling. </li><li>Chile regulates honey imports with a focus on accurate origin documentation and health compliance. </li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/South_America.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_yfAHjT": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Europe</h3><ul><li>Classified as a novel food in most European countries. </li><li>Must comply with EU labeling standards  </li><li>Involves evaluation of the composition of honey, potential risks, and the intended conditions of use for the authorization process. </li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Europe.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_ixkTkh": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Asia</h3><ul><li><strong>Nepal and Turkey:</strong> <a href=\"https://medicinalmadhoney.com\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Authentic Mad Honey\">Mad honey</a> is traditionally harvested and legally sold.</li><li><strong>India:</strong> Yes, Mad Honey legal in India. As, Mad honey is not explicitly banned but must meet <a href=\"https://www.fssai.gov.in/cms/food-safety-and-standards-regulations.php\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Food Safety and Standards Authority of India (FSSAI)</span></a> regulations.</li><li><strong>China and Southeast Asia:</strong> Legal for sale and consumption, but subject to food safety laws with restrictions on psychoactive effects.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Asia.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_DHJ3Vg": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Africa</h3><ul><li>Legal to sell or consume in most African countries.</li><li>The Agricultural Product Standards Act(1990) regulates honey and bee product sales. </li><li>Both local and imported must comply with regulations including grading, packaging, and labeling requirements. </li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Africa.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        },
        "block_6ptQDL": {
          "type": "block",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Antartica</h3><ul><li>No food regulations; governed by international treaties.</li><li>Imported food must comply with the laws of the managing country.</li><li>Antarctic Treaty protocols require waste minimization and contamination prevention.</li><li>Stations prioritize food safety and adhere to biosecurity measures.</li><li>Environmental integrity is maintained through strict waste management.</li></ul>",
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Antarctica.jpg",
            "svg": ""
          }
        }
      },
